limate and is an excellent place to relax in the laps of nature amidst nothing but beauty. People usually visit Shimla, along with Kasauli, as it has a number of spots worth visiting. Maximum tourists are from North India, who want to escape from their busy city lives, and wish to have a change of atmosphere. The air in the mountains is not just cool but also fresh and breezy, unlike the city air, which is immensely polluted. However, the heavenly beauty of this place attracts people from other parts of India and outside of India too. Here's a list of places in and near Kasauli that you can visit if you plan to explore the alluring state of Himachal Pradesh- 1. Monkey point Kasauli's Monkey Point is considered to be the highest point in this town, and it is considered to be one of the most well-known tourist attractions in the area. The point is situated just four kilometers from the bus stop. A small temple devoted to Lord Hanuman is situated here that is filled with monkeys. The Monkey Point is the highest point of the town and offers a splendid view of the surrounding towns of Chandigarh, Kalka, Panchkula, and Sutlej River. If the weather is clear, it is possible to see the snow-covered summit of 'Choor Chandni', the highest peak in the Lower Himalayan belt. According to local legend, when Lord Hanuman brought the Sanjeevani herb to aid Laxman, his foot touched the place. An astonishing fact about this place is that this hill's top has been shaped like a foot. The temple is believed to be engraved due to Lord's footmark. "Tapp's Nose" was the name used to describe the unique design of the stone. Timings: 9 AM - 5 PM 2. Mall Road Kasauli is a small, tranquil town with little hustle-bustle. A mall road is a great option for spending your evening in slightly chilly weather. There are numerous shops selling local items as well as woolen clothes. There are small cafes and 'dhabas' offering all kinds of foods to cater to your taste. Some cafes have a very pleasant vibe with talented people singing and playing instruments like guitar. Markets are at their most vibrant in the early evenings, and a stroll in the evening can be highly recommended. 3. Christ (Anglican) Church The church is situated in the center of the city, with an enticing mall road that runs around the church. This is a well-known tourist attraction. It was built in the year 1853 and was designed with the splendor of the Gothic architectural style. The church is adorned with beautiful Italian as well as Spanish stained-glass window that depicts Christ, Mary, Saint Barnabas, and Saint Francis, and it is a stunning structure to admire. It is a peaceful and serene spot and a must-visit for any tourist visiting Kasauli. 4. Kalka-Shimla Toy Train It is believed that the Kalka route from the Shimla journey is most effectively traveled using the toy train, which operates on a narrow-gauge track. It is famous for its stunning views of the surrounding hills and villages. The historical Kalka-Shimla Toy train has made its way to the UNESCO World Heritage List. It offers the passengers a beautiful journey amidst the green hills and forests of Pine and Deodar. The route was carved through the lush natural beauty throughout Himachal Pradesh during British rule. Therefore, this train journey is sure to transport you back to a totally different time in the past and on some of the most beautiful train journeys in India. The five-and-a-half-hour toy train trip offers a variety of services, and you should definitely travel via it. 5. Gilbert Trail A natural trail that runs through lush green hills and an enchanting background sound of birds hooting and chirping is what makes Gilbert Trail one of Kasauli's most beautiful spots to explore. It's only 0.9 miles of stone trail that will take you into the awe-inspiring world filled with the captivating beauty of Nature. We'd recommend taking a detour once the main trail is finished and then hiking for an additional 300m to the top of the mountain. From here, you'll be able to relish the stunning panorama of the town and click pictures to treasure as memories. The morning is the ideal time to go on this trail. It would help if you were cautious while walking and should not hike on a nature trail during the evening because they can be slippery. Timings: 6 AM until 5 PM 6. Sunrise point It's hard to get up in the morning and catch the first light. But all that pain disappears when the sun's rays warm your skin, and the sky begins to dance in vibrant hues of red, orange, and pink. This Kasauli tourist spot is located in the Lower Mall. This area was previously known as Hawa Ghar. You can enjoy a spectacular sunrise view from this area early in the morning, but you can also go to the area later in the day to capture the beauty of Nature with your cameras. This is why it is one of the most popular places in Kasauli. The best strategy is to google the time of sunrise or ask the locals and reach the spot before time so that you don't miss your chance of seeing the dazzling yellow star of our galaxy. 7. Sunset point Although both sunrise and sunset have their charm, if you can't get up early to witness the sunrise, the town has a sunset point, making it one of the most sought-after places in Kasauli. Himachal Pradesh has some of the most beautiful sunsets in entire India. To catch the stunning sunset, you should arrive a bit early. Relax, set your camera to timelapse and capture these moments. You can then relive them over and over again. Enjoy a snack and then relish the bright colors of the sunset as they illuminate the sky of Kasauli. The tourist spots in Kasauli are ideal for nature lovers, photographers, and couples looking to enjoy serendipity. It is a natural phenomenon, so the exact time of sunset can change. To find out the exact sunset time, you can google it or ask the locals there. 8. Gurkha Fort One of the most impressive places in Kasauli is the Gurkha Fort. It is situated in the Parwanoo region of Subathu, a town in Kasauli. The 180-year-old canons, which were used in the Gurkha wars, are its pride, and it has ancient frescos on its walls. Both history and nature lovers will find this place to be super interesting. This area is surrounded by dense shrubs, eucalyptus, and pine forests. This fort is now a well-known training facility for the army's Gurkha regiment. The entire area offers stunning views that make it worth taking incredible photographs. Spring is the best season to visit Kasauli and explore this tourist destination. Timings: 9 AM to 6 PM 9. Kasauli Brewery The Kasauli hill station provides some relief from the scorching heat, even in the summer. And this brewery is like icing on the cake as it is a great place to visit in Kasauli for those who need to cool down. This is one of the oldest breweries in the entire nation and is also known as Solan Brewery. Edward Dyer, one of Asia's oldest Scotch whiskey distilleries, founded this place in 1820. After exploring the area, you can sit down with your loved ones to enjoy a glass or two of wine until late evening. Entry fees are INR 250 per person. There are separate costs for the beer menu. Timings: 7 AM to 7 PM 10. Timber trail The Timber Trail Resort has spanned over two hills and is linked by a cable car. The ropeway is a thrilling experience in itself. It runs from the resort to Timber Hill heights and can take up to 12 people in one go. It covers a distance of about 2 kilometers in 10 minutes. The area is indeed a charming part of town. Parwanoo in Himachal Pradesh is where the resort is. It is approximately 40 kilometers from Kasauli and is an amazing spot to visit with friends and family. The resort is located on top of a mountain with pine forests. It offers spectacular views of the whole town and the twisting and turning Kaushalya River. This is a great spot to watch sunsets. Timings: 7 AM to 7 PM Next TopicTourist Places in Paris ? prev next ? For Videos Join Our Youtube Channel: Join Now